Well, I made it so when you move the mouse out of the tbody, it blurs the contenteditabe... the reason is if you have a contenteditable un-saved, and you move the mouse to click the header to sort. A problem occurs where the table gets sorted, then the "updateCell" method gets triggered to update the cell contents, but the row indexing is all messed up because it was just sorted.

You can try to disable this, and see if this is turns out to be a non-issue for you.... in the `initialized` callback, add this:

```js
initialized: function(table){
  table.config.$tbodies.off('mouseleave.tseditable');
}

