We prefer a subfolder because we are deploying our own web-app alongside luigi which receives Luigi events and utilises the json api.  So from the users perspective it is one app at one URL.

I agree that it might be better if the Luigi webserver was completely prefix-aware but on brief testing this is enough for us.  We can use nginx URL rewriting to make the webapp work without being aware of a prefix.  This appears to be enough:

    location ~ /luigi(?<path>.*) {
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
        proxy_set_header Host $http_host;
        proxy_set_header X-NginX-Proxy true;
        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8082$path$is_args$args;
        proxy_redirect off;
        proxy_http_version 1.1;

    }

